[Cheshire,

December, 1884.] Connolly v. Waycott. Assumpsit for labor. D. H. Woodward, for the plaintiff. Lane Sf Dole and E. B. Ohamplin, for the defendant. Carpenter, J.

No question of law is presented. Whether the labor was performed upon the credit of the defendant, or upon that of Knapp, was a question of fact. •

Exceptions overruled.

Blodgett, J., did not sit: the others concurred.
